entries.title: Russia's Basic Errors Jeopardize Its Ukraine Forces, Military Analysts Say
entries.description: Cellphone use and the storage of ammunition near troops are called indicative of poor operational discipline.

entries.title: EU Set to Impose Coordinated Controls on Travelers From China
entries.description: China has warned against measures such as mandatory pre-travel tests for travelers.

entries.title: Saudi Crown Prince Tangles With Sovereign Wealth Fund Over How to Invest Oil Riches
entries.description: Prince Mohammed bin Salman has vexed financial officials at times as he pushes pet projects on the Public Investment Fund, including a deal with Jared Kushner.

entries.title: China Rails Against Covid Restrictions on Its Citizens
entries.description: Beijing warns of unspecified countermeasures, as holiday tourism spending and box office receipts point to a sluggish economic rebound at home.

entries.title: U.K. Faces New Wave of Strikes as Workers Fight for Higher Pay
entries.description: British unions representing public-sector workers have spent months battling the government over pay rises that haven’t come close to matching the country’s inflation rate, which is near a 40-year high.

entries.title: German Facility, Built at Breakneck Speed, Accepts Gas Shipment From U.S.
entries.description: The shipment arrived at the LNG import terminal in the port town of Wilhelmshaven, a facility that was built in less than a year to help Germany avert an energy shortage.

entries.title: Ukraine Repels Russian Drone Attacks With Help From Western-Supplied Air Defenses
entries.description: Kyiv is getting better at intercepting Iranian-made Shahed drones that Russia has relied on to damage Ukrainian infrastructure.

entries.title: Israeli Far-Right Leader Ben-Gvir Visits Flashpoint Jerusalem Site
entries.description: Palestinians called the move a provocation amid concerns about the new government expanding Israeli control over the holy compound.

entries.title: Ukraine Has Digitized Its Fighting Forces on a Shoestring
entries.description: Ukraine has achieved a cut-price version of what the Pentagon has spent decades and billions of dollars striving to accomplish: digitally networked fighters, intelligence and weapons.

entries.title: Mourners Bid a Quiet Farewell to Pope Benedict
entries.description: Thousands have filed past Benedict’s body lying in state in St. Peter’s Basilica, though nothing like the enormous lines that formed for St. John Paul II in 2005.
